Informative and compelling at times, yet hardly deserving of the two Academy Awards it garnered; SPOTLIGHT seats Michael Keaton and Mark Ruffalo [Hulk] at the helm, to pragmatically delineate the investigative reporting that exposed Boston√¢(TM)s Catholic Archdiocese Sex Abuse Scandal. It√¢(TM)s no more or less than what anyone would expect, with a few inquisitive surprises to keep the ball rolling. The film is worth seeing once for its academic dramatization value, but that√¢(TM)s about it.
