While it wasn't my first reaction when I sat down to watch "Spotlight," I did have a nagging feeling in the back of my brain as it started that this could just be one of those "Award Bait" films that overdoes its drama, tries really hard to make it look artsy without really injecting anything creative and overflowing its cast with lots of big name actors in order to buy itself some gravitas.  Thankfully, the movie proved to be none of that as it was a fantastically acted, extremely grounded in its drama and the whole thing felt very real and meaningful.  It has no flash and the presentation is fairly by-the-numbers but it is in the real-feel drama it provides and the ridiculously sympathetic and realistic performances that make this story adapted from real life very engaging and emotional.  The only drawback I had for the film is that I don't see a lot of replay potential in it for me but that doesn't stop it from being a truly amazing film.

