Spotlight is directed by Tom McCarthy, and stars Michael Keaton, Rachel McAdams, Mark Ruffalo, Billy Crudup, and many more. The film is about several scandals surrounding Catholic priests, who have molested children within the Church. From the very first seen, audiences can feel the sadness and quietness of the community, and how it reflects the world's initial reaction to this. From the incredible performances from a powerhouse cast, brilliant direction, and superb writing Spotlight is a terrific motion picture. Every bit of screen time matters, and the dramatic elements draw you into the film. It was highly deserving of best picture(at the Oscars), and is a must see.
