"Spotlight" was destined to be one of the most controversial movies of 2015, but definitely also one of the most successful. The characters in the movie are definitely the strong part and all the actors and actresses deliver strong and believable performances that are to be remembered. Mark Ruffalo, however, steals the show and he makes us all forget that he is also the man who plays a big green monster in a completely different franchise. He is surrounded by strong secondary players like Michael Keaton and Stanley Tucci who also show their great range. However, the movie falters when it comes to the entertainment value and ultimately fails in making a great and compelling story because of its constant attempt to remind people that this is still something that happens today. Don't get me wrong, I understand the importance of the message, but when a movie constantly hits you over the head with references of today's problems, it just ends up being too much and that's why I felt the urge to walk away from the movie multiple times. This is a good movie, but it could have been much better than it ended up being.
