It's amazing how a film so uncinematic can be so captivating. This is bare bones cinematography, but I think that's intentional. I think McCarthy and Takayanagi wanted to put the spotlight (pun fully intended) on the actors and let them and the story carry the film. And it paid off! Spotlight is a thoroughly engaging, almost documentary-like film!
