Spotlight is a carefully crafted film that delicately balances objective fact with overwhelming pathos. Every moment provides an opportunity for the filmmakers to emotionally attack the Catholic Church, but instead it allows the characters to tell the story through their objective journey. The characters are represented by a stellar ensemble cast with Mark Ruffalo earning an Academy Award nomination for Best Supporting Actor. The dialogue is smooth and perfect when told by the cast. The words are soaked with wit and humor; an impressive feat for a film addressing such urgent truths. Tom McCarthey's directing is concise, and allows the actors to steal the show. Perhaps the movie lacks a climax, but the calm story telling accentuates the somber ending and gives the movie its gravity.
A truly compelling and devastating story that pulls you in from the start along with an all-star cast who give the performances of their careers.
