From those nominated for best picture at the Oscars, this was a worthy winner - although personally I thought the field weak this year. This is a slow burner gradually gaining pace as the story unravels. As much about the process of getting news as the news itself. Wonderfully shot with the backdrop of a claustrophobic Boston trying to protect itself from outsiders. Superbly acted from the top billers (especially Michael Keaton on a roll now) right down to the victims. Only minus for me is the depiction of 911 in the events seen more as an annoyance to proceedings rather than an emotional event.
