This year's Best Picture Oscar winner is an excellent film and real eye-opener. Of course, I knew a lot about the priest scandals within the Catholic Church, but I had no idea how extensive it was in one city! The Boston Globe investigation not only uncovers the abuses themselves, but the cover-ups that go way up the church hierarchy. Though the reporters work is shown as being heroic, the movie doesn't let the media off the hook, either. Fine performances all around, with Mark Ruffalo the standout. I docked this a half star because I would've liked to have seen more about the immediate fallout once the articles went public, especially now that it's a world-wide scandal. A minor complaint, really. There are so few really good films about the world of journalism. This is definitely one of them - see it!
