Spotlight is an interesting look at the process of investigative journalism conducted by the reporters of the Boston Globe. The subject was the major lift of the veil of the crimes by priests in the Catholic church. I found it interesting. Most definitely top honors go to Mark Ruffalo, Liev Schreiber, and Stanley Tucci. The ensemble does an impeccable job to deliver the goods. It would be going over old ground otherwise, because this news issue has been examined quite often.  I found that it played very much like a quality TV movie. Perhaps this might be a stepping stone for a future TV series...but cinema I feel should not only deal with hard hitting issues, but also deliver a completely new perspective on any historic event. Also the screenplay did not really shed any further light or insight beyond what has already been discussed. Perhaps I am looking for something more of a revelation on the outcome, or a character transformation. The screenplay did not deliver answers, but certainly got people to discuss faith and trust issues. It does deals with the subject matter with dignity.
