An important story. Well acted, well told, well made all around. Not flashy -- in fact, it's done in an almost ordinary, reporterly, investigative fashion -- and that's how it shines. From there the story truly breathes and captures (and builds and maintains) interest.
one of those movies you keep hearing how great it is, and then you see it and it actually does not disappoint...in an era still of an overwhelming amount of anti heroes, this movie manages to nail the tricky balance of presenting real feeling people that you can still relate to while respecting and admiring...reminiscent of a mix of old school intelligent Sydney Lumet style tales, esp the Verdict, with the zealotry of All the Presidents Men...it also pulls off another challenge that many movies fail when they attempt: each new character introduced in the first act is a recognizable and terrific actor at the top of his or her game...more to come of my review, but for now, I say this is definitely one of the year's best stories, told simply and well, with a top notch catch, that makes me hope someday i could be in such a movie...but hey, thats ridiculous...anyway, bravo
