I have a soft spot for investigative dramas, especially those that depict the minds behind the investigation. So, it's easy to love "Spotlight"; it uncovers disturbing content and displays it under a journalistic light, but it's handle with such care that you begin to immerse yourself into the film itself. It subtly blew me away, and made me remember why I love the art of writing.
