The feel good movie of the year... pun intended.
It's a big year for true-life films, with The Revenant, The Big Short, and now Spotlight. There's something about watching a film and after seeing those words - "Based on real events" - that makes the story that unfolds that much more enduring. No more true is that than with this true-life journalism, written and directed by Tom McCarthy. 

When you have six actors of the caliber that Spotlight has, it is easy to miss expectations. With an ensemble cast it can be difficult to balance the screen time among the celebrity, but no one actor steals the show, which only furthers the authenticity of the teamwork that takes place on screen. With the continued renaissance of Michael Keaton and similarly off-script castings for the rest, Spotlight delivers a forceful refutation of the powers that be and advocates the continued importance of investigative journalism in today's world.
