You will watch this film with a queasy unease ... it starts slowly as the journalists of 'Spotlight' probe the cover-up to produce their journalistic expose. It's dramatically well paced with good performances all around, no tricks or gimmicks -  the story itself is enough, powerfully re-told, hard not to be unmoved.
Much like 'All the President's Men', only instead of politics its religion. This is the world of investigative journalism and how institutions can help in one of the biggest cover-ups of abuse in the 21st century. This is step by step reporting, yet it moves along at a pace. At the end though, much like 'The Big Short', you wonder if anyone has learnt anything... and if that sort of things stills carry on?  Well worth a watch.
