They don't dwell on the details of the abuse or exploit the brave victims.  The movie speaks more to the systematic cover up not only by the church but also by the judicial system and pretty much everyone else involved which for me was even more disturbing. One moment in the film really struck me - a victim explains that they didn't just lose their innocence, they lost their faith.  For me that was so powerful.  I also appreciated that they showed what a personal struggle it was for the reporters involved to reveal something so disturbing about the church they had all been raised in.  As a Catholic I was concerned that the movie would turn out to be a condemnation of Catholicism as a whole but it isn't.  This is a film worth seeing for anyone irrespective of their religious affiliation.
