A fairly powerful film exploring an interesting facet of the catholic church abuse scandal. Although engaging in an exploration of the heart wrenching child abuse by catholic clergy, the film did not seem to focus on that specific singular emotional impact.  Spotlight explores the interesting process of the local media investigating the abuse scandal that penetrates almost all aspects of the local community in which they live.  Again, a strong appeal to emotions was not the only focus.  At the same time, how could one not emotionally invest in a story of a group of people fighting to expose this horrible egregious violation of the body, mind, and soul of the victims, families, and community.  This film might have warranted another star of a higher rating had this film not had the typical Hollywood film trope of the journalist as classic social justice warrior.  This tired trope left the film with a predictable and unoriginal feel.
