With its journalistic depth and reflective poignancy, Spotlight almost ascends to the greatness of "All The President's Men", and pursues a topic that is frivolously examined but never approached with the keen eye and heavy heart at the same time. Director Tom McCarthy delves into the motivations without preconceptions and gracefully tells the story with tour de force performances by Ruffalo and co. While some may feel the burn of the caustic paint the film uses to illustrate the Catholic Church, the most important thing to take away is that nothing is ever hidden and justice will find its way in the end.
