Since I didn't know anything about the actual stories about SPOTLIGHT, I didn't know what was going to happen. Because of that, I was invested throughout the course of the film. I looked up what the film was about, without looking over specific details, so that I wouldn't get too lost or confused. Even that, it was still hard to follow. But after watching the film, I put together all the events that happened in the story and try to comprehend what I saw. The actors in this film were portrayed perfectly as the team, and their performances are so well executed. That goes for the writing in the script too. It is extremely well-written. The dialogue and how the actors execute it makes for a really interesting and somewhat disturbing story. I also love how the movie was shot. It looks a lot less polished than many films we see today, depicting that it takes place in the early 2000s. I could only think of one flaw in this film. Since it has such a well-known cast, it can be a distraction as we notice who these actors are. But you almost don't notice because they play their parts so well as they don't feel like they are acting, they are real people in this event. I can see how this film is getting a lot of praise and has been receiving multiple movie awards and nominations. But it is a little disturbing at some parts and it is very hard to follow. It's not one of my personal favorite movies of the year, but I acknowledge that it is one of the best of the year.

