It's slow and simplistic. It does the basic minimum and just tells the story of the journalists, however, it doesn't even do it that thoroughly. Certain aspects of the journalists personal lives are hinted at and doors are opened but then they're abandoned. Mark Ruffalo essentially acts the same as he did as the hulk in avengers. The movie also leaves you with a feeling of emptiness like they didn't finish telling the story. They leave out the ramifications of the story.
It feels like a movie made in the 70s, and in a good way. They rarely make movies like these anymore; hard-hitting, critical, and understated. And it's a love letter to investigative journalism, the way it should be. Not bullshit clickbait, but digging deep into stories that matter, come hell or high water.
