Great journalistic movie, probably the best since All the President's Men. Just a well done story based on true events. It doesn't have the natural humor of most of Tom McCarthy's movies, but it does contain the humanism he brings to each of his movies (lets just forget The Cobbler ever happened). The acting is all top notch, and they truly play as an ensemble, no one really gets to out stage any of the others. Probably the best ensemble cast of the year.
The real life story is engagin on its own, but what makes Spotlight stand out is the way director Tom McCarthy develops his characters in different layers and skips all the easy ways of melodrama.
