Today's 10-cent review:  Essentially a recruiting video for journalism, yet done spectacularly well. No unnecessary melodrama, no exploitation of the subject matter, just straight ahead honest to goodness stuff. Which was, fittingly, just like the real work was done. Yes, as a journalist I take pride in seeing these things. But how often is it done this well? ... Beyond that there is the sheer nauseating reaction to seeing what took place, not just in Boston, of course, but all over the world. Though The Globe was the first to so dramatically link the scandal way up the Catholic Church food chain. Also, Boston being so overwhelmingly Catholic, and really such a "small town" for such a big city - the movie did a good job conveying the dynamics of Boston which makes the situation there a bit unique. ... I also, however, despite loathing the Catholic Church as an institution, understand the allure the wanting to believe something and be part of something, and so the disillusionment felt by everyone involved was very touching as well.
