An absolutely fascinating look at the inner workings of top-class investigative journalism.  Outside of the New York Times (and a few other publications), this kind of journalism probably doesn't exist anymore following the advent of the internet.  But it's still amazing to see how a tenacious group of people can work doggedly against all odds at uncovering the truth about a scandal for months on end.  The acting is amazing - with Mark Ruffalo and Michael Keaton delivering particularly impressive performances.
