Given the strength and importance of its fact based story, Spotlight, although well acted and made, lacks a punch that is very much necessary. The film makes you feel as though nothing is at stake, there is hardly any tension, no struggle and most of all, even though the film never lionizes its heroes, it fails to give them any form of characterization. In the end, Spotlight feels monotonous and the characters seem to be finding evidence just like how you find clues in a treasure hunt, it's just there somewhere waiting for them to be found. They always say throughout the film that the Catholic Church is so powerful and they try everything to cover up, but still not even once the Church do anything to prevent the Spotlight team from doing what they want. As far as films like these are concerned, The Insider is the very best, a must watch.
