An important story told in a linear and rather uninventive fashion.   Spotlight tells a crucial story in our history, but fails to do justice to the tale by conveying it in a rather straightforward and sequential manner.   Solid performances all around, although Ruffalo is overly pronounced with many of his choices.  Liev Shrieber is brilliantly understated and carries weight with his effortless brilliance.  The film is worth seeing and is fairly successful in depicting a crucial topic.  It just doesn't have the inventiveness to make it a truly brilliant and timeless motion picture.
