Towards the end of the film, after the story has been printed, Keaton and Ruffalo sprint through the newspaper offices on a Sunday morning.  A hotline had been set up  for survivors of abuse to call in and speak to the reporters.  As Keaton and Ruffalo reach the doorway of their office, they hear the chorus of phones ringing and see their fellow reporter, played by Rachel McAdams, trying to answer every call.  After spending the better part of a Sunday morning listening to what one can only assume are the worst stories imaginable, she sees her coworkers and gives a small smile.  The story has been reported, the work remains.
