One of the most compelling, dramatic, at times laugh out loud funny, entirely human and well balanced movies I have seen in a very long time. It takes an extremely complicated piece of world (and, in particular, Boston) history and condenses without over-simplifying or losing the complexity and nuance of the events. This beautifully crafted approach to the source material combined with stellar performances from Keaton, McAdams and especially Ruffalo make this an instant Best Picture candidate and a can't miss flick for fans of history, compelling storytelling and fantastic acting. As someone who very clearly remembers these events unfolding, I can't see this movie being made better than it has.
