Utterly compelling docudrama about a group of Boston reporters investigating allegations of abuse within the Catholic Church and finding a much larger problem than anyone could have possibly predicted. Top flight performances from a first-rate cast (Mark Ruffalo, Michael Keaton, Rachel McAdams, Stanley Tucci, John Slattery and Billy Crudup - bolstered by a terrific supporting cast of character actors) and a non-melodramatic yet affecting take on a pertinent issue add up to one of the better journalistic dramas in many years (and leagues ahead of Keaton's hackneyed 1994 film, "The Paper") and a serious award contender.
