The film brings to light a well known subject with lots of previously unknown (at least to me) details that prompted me to fact check the story (it is all too true).  The film is therefore informative in addition to being a very good movie with a top cast.  There are a number of messages to take away from this entertaining film, but none more important than the fact a true free press not solely driven by the financial bottom line, has been the backbone of this country and its ideals as well as freedom itself.  Sadly in today's assault on free speech and drive to print or report only what is safe, sensational, and for profit, this kind of journalism is what may cease to exist even as the crime this story covers flourishes.
