Detailing the events leading up to the Globe's title piece on systemic sexual abuse by priests and cover-up thereof within the Boston archdiocese of the Catholic church, this is great. I don't want to get into too many details, but if you get a chance go watch this. Excellent performances all around, although being very much an ensemble piece it's hard to single out a single member of the core 4 (Keaton, Ruffalo, Adams, D'Arcy) as being the lead. It does a good job of simply portraying the reporters not as heroes, but simply doing their job, and even levels some critiques at them for not spotting the information earlier. Were I to fault this, it's that it's very much an "Oscar" movie, but I must stress that is not in and of itself a bad thing. This takes it's story, and tells it extremely well.
