Spotlight has the makings of a great film: terrific actors that sell every moment on screen and add a real layer of depth to their characters, an incredibly competent director that guides through a marvelous screenplay with ease, and a real life story that's equally as fascinating as the film that resulted from it. Aside from all of this, both the creative force and the true facts behind it, Spotlight is simply a terrific cinematic story about the truth, getting closer to the truth, and the collective efforts that it takes to get to the truth... or not. Regardless of background, regardless of beliefs, and regardless of how much you do or don't care about this story... this is a film that is absolutely worth seeing. It's by far one of the best of 2015.
